cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving machine reading comprehension through incorporating explicit syntactic constraints into attention mechanism. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of pre-trained language models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves designing a new network architecture for better representation learning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a potential category as the paper involves using neural networks to improve machine reading comprehension. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the proposed approach may have applications in image captioning and visual question answering tasks.
